## 2. Component A — Ambition Mass Multiplier

The multiplier is derived from the Compound Annual Growth Rate (CAGR) between current and target AGI over the selected timeframe.

### CAGR Calculation

```
CAGR = (Target AGI / Current AGI)^(1 / Years) − 1
```

### Multiplier Tiers

| CAGR Range | Multiplier | Label | Rationale |
|---|---|---|---|
| < 15% | 1.0x | Organic | Pace penalties apply at face value — maintenance-mode growth |
| 15% – 39% | 1.5x | Active Growth | Execution demands exceed steady state — pace strain is amplified |
| ≥ 40% | 2.0x | Aggressive Scaling | Maximum amplification — revised down from original 2.5x |

> **Multiplier Revision Note:** The original spec listed 2.5x for aggressive scaling. Revised to 2.0x because at 2.5x combined with a realistic Pace load at the 25-point cap, the formula produced scores below 0 in legitimate heavy-friction scenarios, removing the score's ability to differentiate within that territory. At 2.0x, meaningful differentiation is preserved at the lower bands while still communicating that aggressive scaling materially amplifies execution demands.

