## 7. Near-Threshold Watch Signal Logic

When a formula component does **not** fire a deduction but the underlying metric falls within meaningful proximity of a penalty threshold, the system surfaces a **Watch Signal**.

Watch Signals do not affect the GVI score. They provide forward-looking context about structural proximity to risk.

### Proximity Definition

A Watch Signal fires when a metric is **within 15% of a penalty threshold** in the direction of risk.

### Watch Signal Proximity Zones

| Component | Penalty Threshold | Watch Signal Zone |
|---|---|---|
| Retention | < 85% fires | 85% – 88% |
| Profit Margin | < 20% fires | 20% – 23% |
| Concentration | < 10 clients fires | 10 – 11 clients |
| Positioning Pressure | ≥ 25% ACV delta fires | 20% – 24% ACV delta |
| Sales Pace | ≥ 1.5x ratio fires | 1.3x – 1.49x ratio |
| Hiring Pace | ≥ 11% quarterly fires | 8% – 10% quarterly |
| Capacity Utilization | < $160K fires | $160K – $175K / FTE |

### What Watch Signals Are — and Are Not

- ✅ Forward-looking proximity flags
- ✅ Observational in tone — they name a condition and its implication
- ✅ Growth journey context — relevant to where the business is heading
- ❌ Not deductions — they do not affect the GVI score under any circumstances
- ❌ Not warnings — language is never alarming or prescriptive
- ❌ Not always present — only surface when the metric genuinely falls in the proximity zone
- ❌ Not prescriptive — they never tell the founder what to do

### Two UI Surfaces

#### 1. Pressure Family Expandable Cards

Each pressure family has an expandable detail card. When a Watch Signal is active for that family, the card surfaces a brief inline flag — one sentence, observational in tone. Visible only when the founder expands the card. Intentional — rewards curiosity without cluttering the primary output.

**Example — Concentration at 11 clients:**
> *"Client concentration is within threshold at 11 clients — one client departure during the growth period would bring this below the risk boundary."*

**Example — Positioning Pressure at 20.5% ACV delta:**
> *"Target ACV represents a 20.5% increase over current — just below the upmarket shift threshold. If actual pricing moves above [X] during execution, this crosses into scored territory and will increase structural friction."*

#### 2. Bottom Synthesis Narrative

The synthesis at the bottom of the output pulls together the full picture — score, composition label, active deductions, and Watch Signals — into a cohesive plain-language paragraph. Watch Signals appear here as contextual notes woven into the narrative, not listed separately.

> **Implementation note:** Watch Signals are a conditional display layer. Run proximity checks alongside the scoring calculation and populate a separate `watchSignals` flags object. That object feeds both the expandable card layer and the synthesis narrative generator. No new inputs or scoring logic changes required.

